cane Harvey. From Corpus Christi to Galveston, they paint a vivid, compelling picture of heartache and destruction, as well as resilience and recovery, as survivors slowly begin rebuilding their lives and their communities. An emotionally provocative read, Hurricane Harvey’s Aftermath provides insight into how ordinary people experience and persevere through a disaster in an age of environmental vulnerability.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Jun 2022) 0aDisaster reliefzTexas. 0aHurricane Harvey, 2017. 0aHurricane damagezTexas. 0aHurricaneszTexas. 7aSOCIAL SCIENCE / Disasters & Disaster Relief.2bisacsh  aBeginning the Recovery Process.  aBonding Social Capital.  aCharacteristics of Survivors.  aCharacterizing Race and Place.  aCitizen Disaster Communication.  aClimate Risk Perception.  aCommunity Engagement.  aComplicated Impact of Storms.  aData Collection.  aDisaster Mental Health.  aDisaster Response.  aDisaster Risk.  aDisplacement Differences.  aEcological-Based Interventions.  aFederal Disaster Policy.  aFormative Disaster Evaluations.  aFramework for the Book.  aGulf Coast Disaster.  aInclusive Disaster Volunteer Groups.  aInterview Strategies.  aLinking Social Capital.  aNatural Disasters.  aPTSD.  aPosttraumatic Growth.  aPreparedness.  aRace and Place Intersection.  aResilience.  aResiliency and Recovery.  aSetting Records.  aSpatial and Social Disparities.  aSurvivor Locations.  aTime Banking.  aVisual Cues from a Disaster Zone.1 aSpialek, Matthew L., eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2020 Englishz978311070471608iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2020z9783110704518oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package: